# Agent Operating Principles

- Treat user requests as implementation tasks by default unless the user asks for brainstorming only.
- Before making edits, briefly state intent and affected files.
- While working, provide short progress updates for non-trivial tasks.
- After work, report:
  - what changed
  - why it changed
  - what was verified
  - any remaining risks or assumptions
- Do not claim work was done without checking files, code paths, or runtime evidence.
- If uncertain, say exactly what is uncertain and why.
- Prefer minimal, targeted changes over broad rewrites.
- Preserve existing architecture and style unless the user asks for refactors.
- Never silently ignore contradictory requirements; surface conflicts explicitly.
